{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Base the High Income Child Benefit Charge (HICBC) threshold on household income",
        "additional_details": "Child Benefit is claimed and used by families/households, however, the HICBC is assessed on an individual income of \u00a360K or more within any given household. That means a two-parent household could earn up to \u00a3120K (up to \u00a360K each) before being eligible for the charge, however, a two-parent or single parent household that relies on the income of one parent earning anything over \u00a360K is obligated to pay the HICBC. We think this is unfair and negates the value of claiming child benefit.",
        "background": "The aim of this petition is to request the government to change the threshold for the High Income Child Benefit Charge (HICBC) from the current individual \u00a360K income to a household income of \u00a3120K.",
